{
  "stem": "1568.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You-- you gave away your precious things that you had before to get a piece of bread and butter to exist.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I believe it was around December 1942-- no, it was maybe a September 1942-- that we found out that there's going to be a-- [INAUDIBLE] send out the people out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you got up in the morning and again, like in '39, you would see people dead on the streets.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And those were, I guess, the first casualties of intellects, of people who did something wrong or just were on the list of the Germans who were shot on this particular night.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also, I guess it was an unlucky and lucky situation for me, that in 1942, I got sick of typhus, still in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Didn't go to a hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm talking about my mom.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her love, her ingenuity, was able to cure me out of typhus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think that indirectly, saved my life too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But telling the later story.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyway, in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 1943, I believe, I can't-- yeah, it's '43 when the ghetto was sent out-- and the way we found out that they did not let us go like we were going out in the morning to work and then-- they did not let us go to-- back home at night.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They told us that that's what going to happen, that they're going to send out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But not to worry, that all the family members of the workers will be put in a special place and they would be-- gonna be saved.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at that time, I believe there were about 7,000 people sent out.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
